@Example.API_HostAddress = http://localhost:5010

### Seed demo data (run once to populate tables)
POST {{Example.API_HostAddress}}/auth/seed

###

### Value Convertor + Procedure: lookup by username (case-insensitive — "Alice" stored as "alice")
GET {{Example.API_HostAddress}}/auth/login/Alice
Accept: application/json

###

### Same lookup lowercase — same result
GET {{Example.API_HostAddress}}/auth/login/alice
Accept: application/json

###

### JOIN: courses enrolled by a user (replace with userId returned from /auth/seed)
GET {{Example.API_HostAddress}}/auth/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/courses
Accept: application/json

###

### Set Operation (UNION): all distinct courses
GET {{Example.API_HostAddress}}/auth/courses
Accept: application/json

###
